# Symplet Privacy Policy

Effective Date: June 5, 2025

## Introduction

Symplet ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and share information when you use our mobile application (the "App").

## Information We Collect

### Information You Provide Directly
- Supplement Tracking: Information about supplements you add to your personal stack and dosages


### Information We Collect Automatically
- Custom Supplement Creation: When you create custom supplements, we collect the supplement name, category (optional), and source where you heard about it (optional) for anonymous market research
- Local Supplement Tracking: Information about supplements you add to your personal list is stored locally on your device only

### Information from Third Parties
- Affiliate Click Tracking Only: When you click on purchase links, we track clicks for commission purposes (no personal information is shared with retailers)

## How We Use Your Information

We use the collected information to:
- Provide Our Service: Display relevant supplement recommendations and celebrity profiles

## Information Sharing and Disclosure

We may share your information in the following circumstances: 

### Affiliate Program Participation
- Amazon Associates: When you click affiliate links, Amazon receives anonymous click data but no personal information

### Legal Requirements
We may disclose information if required by law or to:
- Comply with legal processes or government requests
- Protect our rights, property, or safety
- Prevent fraud or illegal activities
- Respond to emergencies involving personal safety

### Business Transfers
If Symplet is involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale, information may be transferred as part of that transaction.

## Your Rights and Choices

You have the following rights regarding your personal information:

### Communication Preferences
- Notifications: Control push notifications in your device settings

### Data Portability
- Export: Request a copy of supplement tracking data in a portable format

## Data Retention

We retain your information for as long as necessary to provide our services:
- Aggregate Data: Non-personal, aggregate data may be retained indefinitely for research and business purposes

## Children's Privacy

Symplet is not intended for children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13 or anyone using the app for that matter. If we become aware that we have collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete such information promptly.

## Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes:
- Effective Date: The updated policy will include a new effective date
- Continued Use: Continued use of the App after changes constitutes acceptance of the updated policy

## California Privacy Rights (CCPA)

If you are a California resident, you have additional rights:
- Right to Know: Request information about data collection and sharing
- Right to Non-Discrimination: We won't discriminate against you for exercising your rights
- Right to Opt-Out: Opt-out of the sale of personal information (Note: We do not sell personal information)

## Contact Us

If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us:

Email: nick@paytonsplace.net  
Response Time: We aim to respond to privacy inquiries within 30 days

## Supplement Disclaimer

Symplet provides information for educational purposes only. The information in our App:
- Is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure, or prevent any disease
- Should not replace professional medical advice
- Is based on publicly available research and celebrity statements
- Individual results may vary

Always consult with a healthcare professional before starting any new supplement regimen.

